article.headline: UC Irvine 66, UC Santa Barbara 63
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Patrick Sanders scored 16 points and Brett Lauer tied a career high with 14 points to lead UC Irvine past UC Santa Barbara 66-63 on Thursday night. Darren Fells added 12 points and 13 rebounds for the Anteaters (12-4, 1-2 Big West). Alex Harris led the Gauchos (12-4, 1-2) with 15 points and Ivan Elliott and Paul Roemer scored 12 apiece. UC Irvine led 64-52 after a 3-pointer by Lauer with 5:53 remaining but UC Santa Barbara then forced the Anteaters into six turnovers and scored five points in a 20-second stretch that cut the lead to 64-63 with 1:10 left. Sanders missed the front end of a one-and-one with 13.3 seconds remaining and the Gauchos set up for a shot to take the lead, but Harris lost the ball with two seconds left. Sanders then made a pair of free throws in the final second.
